		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Making such a cart looks like an awfully complicated task for a single person, specially if this person has to *ask* about how to do it. =)
<br />
<br />Seriously, the PowerPak is probably the best choice. Even if you were able to connect a cart to your PC via USB (which is a pretty complicated task, or so I heard), you'd still have to deal with the different mappers, unless you wanted to develop for a single mapper, forever, but that seems like a very dull feature for a devcart.
<br />
<br />Also, if you had only one mapper, you wouldn't even be able to play many commercial games, except for the ones using the same mapper as your devcart, so it would be strictly for dev'ing alright.
<br />
<br />However, mappers still seem to be a problem with the PowerPak, because complicated mappers such as the MMC3 do not seem to behave the same as the real thing.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


